            "answer_text": "Well, Homer\u2019s Iliad is usually considered the foundational text of Western Literature, so that\u2019s a good place to start. The three great tragedians - Aeschylus, Euripides and Socrates wrote plays that are still performed around the world both in the original Greek and in translation. If comedy is more to your taste, then take a look at Aristophanes. And in the field of Philosophy there s a plethora of names that are still considered in modern University courses - Plato, Aristotle, Zeno etc. For History buffs, Herodotus, Thucydides and Xenophon are essential. I could go on and on - but I won\u2019t. ",
